data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Standard Push:</b>
If you are working on the <code data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0" data-index-in-n=
ode=3D"45">main</code> branch and your remote is named <code data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"3,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"82">origin</code> (the default), use:
<code data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"109">git push origi=
n main</code></p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0"><b data-path-to-no=
de=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">First Time Pushing a New Branch:</b>
If you just created a branch locally and want to link it to the server, use=
 the <code data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"113">-u</code>=
 (upstream) flag:
<code data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"133">git push -u or=
igin &lt;your-branch-name&gt;</code></p><blockquote data-path-to-node=3D"3,=
1,1"><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,1,0">This "sets the upstream," meaning in =
the future, you can just type <code data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,1,0" data-inde=
x-in-node=3D"67">git push</code> while on that branch.</p></blockquote></li=
><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0" data-ind=
ex-in-node=3D"0">Pushing All Branches:</b>
If you want to sync every branch you've worked on to the remote:
<code data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"87">git push --all =
origin</code></p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"4"><h3 data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"5">The Workflow Context</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"6">Before you push=
, ensure your changes are staged and committed, otherwise there will be not=
hing to "send" to the server.</p><ol start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=3D"7"><l=
i><p data-path-to-node=3D"7,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"7,0,0" data-index-=
